Some 
 literature (e.g., Suri et al. [abs-2301-03980]) suggested, perhaps provocatively, 
 that LLMs 
 will render explicit KGs obsolete:
 if machines can 
 understand
 all digital content on the Internet,
 why should 
 we put effort into structuring data and knowledge? 
 From the previous examples, and as we will argue herein, this view is 
 not justified. 
 Rather the growing consensus -- and a growing body of research -- indicates that LLMs and KGs complement each other
 [DBLP:journals/corr/abs-2306-08302,DBLP:journals/corr/abs-2306-11489,DBLP:journals/corr/abs-2308-10168,DBLP:journals/tgdk/PanRKSCDJO0LBMB23].